        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:02PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurel Fork, or 7 miles southwest of Willis, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Willis...
Laurel Fork...
Meadows Of Dan...
and Mabry Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
